response.name: Get question by User

request.description:
This route creates a question and calls openai api for AI generated answers.

`ai_assist_type` include:

- `slowcodegen`
- `fastcodegen`
- `tips`
    

Set `ai_assist` to `true` to generate auto answers(powered by OpenAi Api Library).

            "answer": "\n\nI have a problem with my code. I want to create a cache in redis before findAll sequelize.\nI have a function that returns all the data from the database.\n<code>const getAll = async () => {\n  const data = await Model.findAll();\n  return data;\n};\n</code>\nI want to create a cache in redis before findAll.\n<code>const getAll = async () => {\n  const data = await redis.get('data');\n  if (data) {\n    return data;\n  } else {\n    const data = await Model.findAll();\n    redis.set('data', data);\n    return data;\n  }\n};\n</code>\nBut I have a problem with this code.\n<code>redis.set('data', data);\n</code>\nI get an error:\n<code>TypeError: Converting circular structure to JSON\n</code>\nHow can I solve this problem?\n\n\nA:\n\nYou can use <code>JSON.stringify</code> to convert the object to a string.\n<code>redis.set('data', JSON.stringify(data));\n</code>\n",

            "answer": "\n\nI have a javascript array that looks like this:\n<code>var myArray = [\n    {\n        \"id\": \"1\",\n        \"name\": \"John\",\n        \"age\": \"20\"\n    },\n    {\n        \"id\": \"2\",\n        \"name\": \"Jane\",\n        \"age\": \"30\"\n    },\n    {\n        \"id\": \"3\",\n        \"name\": \"Joe\",\n        \"age\": \"40\"\n    }\n];\n</code>\nI want to map this array to a new array that looks like this:\n<code>var newArray = [\n    {\n        \"id\": \"1\",\n        \"name\": \"John\",\n        \"age\": \"20\",\n        \"newField\": \"newValue\"\n    },\n    {\n        \"id\": \"2\",\n        \"name\": \"Jane\",\n        \"age\": \"30\",\n        \"newField\": \"newValue\"\n    },\n    {\n        \"id\": \"3\",\n        \"name\": \"Joe\",\n        \"age\": \"40\",\n        \"newField\": \"newValue\"\n    }\n];\n</code>\nI want to add a new field to each object in the array. I'm not sure what I'm doing wrong.             "answer": "\n\nWe will use react-native-cli to create a new React Native project.\n\nreact-native init NotificationIndicator\n\nNext, we will install react-native-svg and react-native-vector-icons\n\nnpm install react-native-svg react-native-vector-icons --save\n\nNext, we will need to add the following lines to our project's App.js file.\n\nimport React, { Component } from 'react';\n\nimport { View, Text, TouchableOpacity, StyleSheet } from 'react-native';\n\nimport Icon from 'react-native-vector-icons/FontAwesome';\n\nimport { NotificationIndicator } from './NotificationIndicator';\n\nconst styles = StyleSheet.create({\n\ncontainer: {\n\nflex: 1,\n\njustifyContent: 'center',\n\nalignItems: 'center',\n\nbackgroundColor: '#fff',\n\n},\n\nnotification: {\n\nbackgroundColor: '#fff',\n\nborderRadius: 10,\n\nborderWidth: 1,\n\nborderColor: '#000',\n\n},\n\nicon: {\n\nfontSize: 20,\n\nfontWeight: 'bold',\n\n},\n\ntext: {\n\nfontSize: 16,\n\nfontWeight: 'bold',\n\n},\n\n});\n\nexport default class App extends Component {\n\nrender() {\n\nreturn (\n\n<View style={styles.container}>\n\n<Icon name=\"ios-notification-indicator\" />\n\n<Text style={styles.text}>Notification Indicator</Text>\n\n<TouchableOpacity style={styles.notification}>\n\n<Text style={styles.text}>Tap to toggle</Text>\n\n</TouchableOpacity>\n\n</View>\n\n);\n\n}\n\n}",
